  "text": "The present work supports the concept that the behaviour of cells studied after several passages in vitro, at least in part, reflects their genetic background. The association between SF behaviours and DN risk was first reported in regards to (NHE-1) activity [9,10]. Subsequently, with similar numbers of subjects, we showed that type 1 diabetic siblings concordant for DN lesions [13] and for DN risk [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] were also concordant for NHE-1 activity [12] and concluded that this was likely, to a large extent, substantially genetically determined.",
